reviews.review: movie keep me going from start to finish
Amazing modern take on a “whodunit” murder mystery!

Full of entertaining moments and satisfying pacing from writer/director Rian Johnson, Knives Out delivers a twisty whodunit filled with interesting characters, anchored by Daniel Craig's excellent performance.
It was funny and charming until about halfway through, then it really seemed to fall apart and drag on and on.
Loved the movie.  A modern day whodunnit with twists and turns. Must see.
Not what I would call acting, Craig's terrible accent, characters playing vaudville and PREDICTABLE

Rian is a clever story teller that trusts his instincts, and seems to care most about entertaining by connecting dots in unexpected ways. He doesn't expect you to think about the odds of the circumstances, or the different way people would have acted if they actually knew what they later reveal they knew. Once the movie is over, if you're still thinking about what happened, that's enough for him it seems. For many movie goers that's plenty, but there's no depth, the story is laid bare for you with dialogue that tells exactly what he's trying to communicate. There is little art or nuance, it's all so evident what just happened. It's a movie I would never want to watch again or refer to. What's wrong with this movie is just the same trend as Looper and The Last Jedi, it's all entertainment for the moment, and dialogue with the message clear as day.  It's just a movie to pass the time, but it pretends to be grand, when it's just a fascade. I could imagine a movie like this in the hands of Christopher Nolan or David Fincher to be far deeper and less hokey. I've learned my lesson, no more Rian Johnson movies for me.
Great cast but not great character development. A little disappointed!

This film brings a fresh spin on a classic premise. Its funny, gripping and keeps you guessing until the end. Filled with phenomenal performances by the whole cast and amazing direction from Rian Johnson, Knives out is a must see.
